      <h1 class='title'>Departmental Expenditure (Official Residences)</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='commons-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HC Deb 27 October 2003 vol 412 c74WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_74ws' title='Col. 74WS &mdash; HC Deb 27 October 2003 vol 412 c74WS' name='column_74ws' href='#column_74ws' rel='bookmark'>74WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S6CV0412P0-04984'>
        <a name='S6CV0412P0_20031027_CWS2_371'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-howard-flight' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0412P0_20031027_CWS2_371' title='Link to this speech by Mr Howard Flight' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-howard-flight" title="Mr Howard Flight">Mr. Flight</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para" id="S6CV0412P0-04984">To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport how much the Department spent on<span class="italic">(a)</span> maintenance, <span class="italic">(b)</span> renovation, <span class="italic">(c)</span> council tax and <span class="italic">(d)</span> running costs of residential properties used by Ministers and officials in each year since 1997. [134683]</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S6CV0412P0-04985'>
        <a name='S6CV0412P0_20031027_CWS2_372'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-richard-caborn' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0412P0_20031027_CWS2_372' title='Link to this speech by Mr Richard Caborn' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-richard-caborn" title="Mr Richard Caborn">Mr. Caborn</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para" id="S6CV0412P0-04985">DCMS has no responsibility for any such properties.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
